    For a quantitative evaluation of the estimated relationship between text and geography, we assess our model&#8217;s ability to predict the geographic location of unlabeled authors based on their text alone.8 This task may also be practically relevant as a step toward applications for recommending local businesses or social connections.
    A randomly-chosen 60% of authors are used for training, 20% for development, and the remaining 20% for final evaluation.
    We compare several approaches for predicting author location; we divide these into latent variable generative models and discriminative approaches.
